    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.24/325: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-05T18:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 5, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 5—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>314. The Assistant Naval Attaché has received information from a source which he
                    considers very reliable that Wright Cyclone aviation motors for replacement on
                    Russian airplanes fighting with the Madrid Government forces are being sent from
                    the United States via Mexico to Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
